Package org.sopra.api.model

Interface PlantLocation

public interface PlantLocation
Plant location is an interface for a data container that holds both an energy node and the playfield element with the same coordinates.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    double getLocationMultiplicator()
    Returns the location dependent multiplier indicating the percentage of the maximum energy level which can be achieved.
    PlayfieldElement getPlayfieldElement()
    Gets the location's playfield element.
    java.util.Optional<Producer> getProducer()
    Gets the optional of a producer.
    java.util.Optional<TransformerStation> getTransformerStation()
    Gets the optional of a transformer station.
    boolean isBuilt()
    Returns if a plant has been built on this plant location.

  • Method Details

    • getTransformerStation

      java.util.Optional<TransformerStation> getTransformerStation()
      Gets the optional of a transformer station. The transformer station is present if and only if NO power plant has been built on the given playfield element.
      Returns:
      the optional of a transformer station.

    • getProducer

      java.util.Optional<Producer> getProducer()
      Gets the optional of a producer. The producer is present if and only if a power plant has been built on the given playfield element.
      Returns:
      the optional of a producer.

    • getPlayfieldElement

      PlayfieldElement getPlayfieldElement()
      Gets the location's playfield element.
      Returns:
      The playfield element.

    • isBuilt

      boolean isBuilt()
      Returns if a plant has been built on this plant location.
      Returns:
      true, if something has been built in this location and false otherwise.
